<p>It‚Äôs going to take deliberate, focused steps to get the quality where it needs to be. For me, the first few have been a matter of showing up. It‚Äôs hard to improve if you‚Äôre not showing up. This is something that <a href="https://dev.to/lvrbrtsn/on-staying-motivated--4861">others</a> doing the ‚ÄúNovember Daily‚Äù thing have pointed to.</p>

<p>This post and the next few are going to be posts that I‚Äôve spent a little more time setting up and figuring out what I want to articulate. I‚Äôm also going to keep an eye on the reading ease and other statistics <a href="https://wereturtle.github.io/ghostwriter/">Ghostwriter</a> provides. For the moment I‚Äôm not going to do much with them, just look at what I‚Äôm actually doing, so I‚Äôll know where I need to go from there. My target will be a 10<sup>th</sup> grade reading level. It‚Äôs a little higher than the usual recommendation, but is a step better than what I‚Äôve managed with this post. (I‚Äôll put a screenshot at the end)</p>

<p>Having done <a href="/2018/11/Projects-Projects-Projects.html">Projects Projects Projects</a>, I‚Äôve got a good idea of what I really want to do something with (or at least what in the near future I want to focus on), and from there I can build a more structured schedule. Probably won‚Äôt happen by the next post or two, but it should be in place before the end of the week. I‚Äôve got to put the car in the shop which should leave me plenty of time to walk over to the coffee shop and think. :)</p>

